Begin by expanding the left side of the equation using the distributive property of the cross product:

\begin{align*}
(5 \bold{a} + 7 \bold{b}) \times (-\bold{a} + 3 \bold{b}) &= 5\bold{a} \times (-\bold{a} + 3 \bold{b}) + 7\bold{b} \times (-\bold{a} + 3 \bold{b}) \\
