**2. Simplify using properties of the cross product:**

Recall that the cross product of a vector with itself is always the zero vector: $\bold{v} \times \bold{v} = \bold{0}$. Also, the cross product is anti-commutative: $\bold{a} \times \bold{b} = -\bold{b} \times \bold{a}$.  Using these properties, we get:

\begin{align*}
-5\bold{a} \times \bold{a} + 15\bold{a} \times \bold{b} - 7\bold{b} \times \bold{a} + 21\bold{b} \times \bold{b} &= \bold{0} + 15\bold{a} \times \bold{b} + 7\bold{a} \times \bold{b} + \bold{0} \\
