By the Law of Cosines on triangle $AOB,$
\[AB^2 = AO^2 + BO^2 - 2 \cdot AO \cdot BO \cdot \cos \angle AOB.\]Since $AO = BO = R,$ this becomes
\[AB^2 = 2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle AOB.\]Similarly,
\begin{align*}
AC^2 &= 2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle AOC, \\
BC^2 &= 2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle BOC.
\end{align*}Then
\begin{align*}
AB^2 + AP^2 + BP^2 &= 2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle AOB + AP^2 + BP^2, \\
AC^2 + AP^2 + CP^2 &= 2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle AOC + AP^2 + CP^2, \\
BC^2 + BP^2 + CP^2 &= 2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle BOC + BP^2 + CP^2.
\end{align*}Since these three expressions are equal,
\[2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle AOB + AP^2 + BP^2 = 2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle AOC + AP^2 + CP^2 = 2R^2 - 2R^2 \cos \angle BOC + BP^2 + CP^2.\]This simplifies to
\[2R^2 (\cos \angle AOC + \cos \angle BOC - \cos \angle AOB) = 0.\]Since $\angle AOB,$ $\angle AOC,$ and $\angle BOC$ are the angles of triangle $ABC,$ their sum is $180^\circ,$ so
\[\cos \angle AOC + \cos \angle BOC - \cos \angle AOB = 0.\]Hence,
\[AB^2 + AP^2 + BP^2 = AC^2 + AP^2 + CP^2 = BC^2 + BP^2 + CP^2 = \boxed{2R^2}.\]

